</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-39_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-40_ pf-text-1"><strong>Anaphylaxis </strong>- An immediate and severe allergic reaction that can be life-threatening.
























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-42_ pf-text-1"><strong>Epinephrine </strong>- The primary medication used to treat anaphylaxis, administered via an auto-injector (e.g., EpiPen).






























